name: Freshdesk
description: Add a Freshdesk Instance to connect your existing Freshdesk account to the Help Desk Hub, allowing you to manage your incidents, priorities, statuses, users, etc. across multiple Help Desk Elements. You will need your Freshdesk account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: A holder for the notification subscription ID
configuration.description: A holder for the notification subscription ID

configuration.name: Subdomain
configuration.description: The subdomain of your Freshdesk instance (i.e. https://[SUBDOMAIN].freshdesk.com)

configuration.name: Max Page Size (or limit)
configuration.description: Freshdesk Beta Max Page Size (or limit)

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Time of Getting Token or Performing Authentication
configuration.description: Freshdesk Beta Time of Getting Token or Performing Authentication

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used to determine how often to poll the service endpoints (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. If the "event.poller.urls" configuration is defined, this field's value is ignored. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - {     "contacts": {         "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts",         "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at",         "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX",         "pageSize": 10000     } }

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

description_text.x-samplevalue: Test ticket for model generation from CE APIs

due_by.description: Timestamp that denotes when the ticket is due to be resolved

email.description: Email address of the requester. If no contact exists with this email address in Freshdesk, it will be added as a new contact.

email_config_id.description:
ID of email config which is used for this ticket. (i.e., support@yourcompany.com/sales@yourcompany.com)
If product_id is given and email_config_id is not given, product's primary email_config_id will be set

facebook_id.description: Facebook ID of the requester. If no contact exists with this facebook_id, then a new contact will be created.

fr_due_by.description: Timestamp that denotes when the first response is due

fr_escalated.description: Set to true if the ticket has been escalated as the result of first response time being breached

fwd_emails.description: Email address(e)s added while forwarding a ticket

group_id.description: ID of the group to which the ticket has been assigned.?The default value is the ID of the group that is associated with the given email_config_id

is_escalated.description: Set to true if the ticket has been escalated for any reason

phone.description: Phone number of the requester. If no contact exists with this phone number in Freshdesk, it will be added as a new contact. If the phone number is set and the email address is not, then the name attribute is mandatory.

priority.description: Priority of the ticket.?The default value is 1. "Low": 1, "Medium": 2, "High": 3, "Urgent": 4

product_id.description: ID of the product to which the ticket is associated.?

reply_cc_emails.description: Email address added while replying to a ticket

requester_id.description: It will be ignored if the email_config_id attribute is set in the request.

responder_id.description: ID of the agent to whom the ticket has been assigned

source.description:
The channel through which the ticket was created.?The default value is 2. Choices are  "Email": 1,"Portal": 2, "Phone": 3,  "Forum": 4,
"Twitter": 5, "Facebook": 6, "Chat": 7, "MobiHelp": 8, "Feedback Widget": 9,  "Outbound Email": 10, "Ecommerce": 11, "Bot": 12

spam.description: Set to true if the ticket has been marked as spam

status.description: Status of the ticket.?The default Value is 2.  "2": [ "Open", "Being Processed" ], "3": [ "Pending", "Awaiting your Reply" ], "4": [ "Resolved", "This ticket has been Resolved" ], "5": [ "Closed", "This ticket has been Closed" ], "6": [ "Waiting on Customer", "Awaiting your Reply" ], "7": [ "Waiting on Third Party", "Being Processed" ]

subject.description: Subject of the ticket.?The default Value is null.
subject.x-samplevalue: Ticket for models CE api fired

tags.description: Tags that have been associated with the ticket

to_emails.description: Email addresses to which the ticket was originally sent

twitter_id.description: Twitter handle of the requester. If no contact exists with this handle in Freshdesk, it will be added as a new contact.

type.description: Helps categorize the ticket according to the different kinds of issues your support team deals with.?The default Value is null.
